Get metadata for a STATcube table

Source: R/table_meta.R
sc_meta.Rd

Functions to extract metadata from a sc_table object.

sc_meta(response)

sc_meta_field(response, i = 1)

Arguments

response

An object of class sc_table
i

index of the field, for which further metadata are desired

See also

Other functions for /table: sc_table(), sc_write_json()

Examples

my_response <- sc_example("population_timeseries.json") %>%
  sc_table()
sc_meta(my_response)

#> $database
#>                                                label         code
#> 1 Population at the beginning of the year since 1982 debevstandjb
#> 
#> $measures
#>    label     code fun precision
#> 1 Number F-ISIS-1 SUM         0
#> 
#> $fields
#>              label        code nitems        type
#> 1     Time section     C-A10-0     39 Time (year)
#> 2       Bundesland    C-BB00-0     10    Category
#> 3 Country of birth C-GEBLAND-0      2    Category
#> 
sc_meta_field(my_response, 1)

#>    label     code     parsed
